I can think of another use for random selection in a name server.
Suppose I have several terminal servers that I am using as milking
machines to provide Telnet into a large host.  One terminal server
isn't enough, I must have 2 or more.  I would rather not tell the
users different names for them, as they are really providing the
same service.  Having the name server randomly select one is one way
of attempting to balance the load.  Perhaps there is another
solution, however.

